==English==

===Etymology===
From ''Chauvin,'' a very patriotic soldier in the French play ''La Cocarde Tricolore'' (after Nicolas ''Chauvin fl'' 1815 legendary French soldier very devoted to Napoleon) + ''[[-isme]]'' -ism

* ''Chauvinism'' originally referred only to an excessive nationalism or patriotism, but its use has broadened.

===Noun===
'''chauvinism'''

# Unwarranted bias, favoritism, or devotion to a particular group, cause, or idea.
#:''Feminists say that male '''chauvinism''' is still prevalant in cultures worldwide.''
#:''Masculinists say that female '''chauvinism''' is still prevalent in cultures worldwide.'' 
# A bias in favour of the familiar.

